Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION congratulating Rising Stars of
2 Indiana.
3 Whereas, Every year the Indiana Association of School
4 Principals accepts nominations of high school juniors for the
5 Rising Stars of Indiana honor roll;
6 Whereas, Rising Stars of Indiana is a non-competitive
7 recognition program designed to honor high school juniors for
8 their exceptional academic achievement;
9 Whereas, The following students were among those
10 nominated to the Rising Stars of Indiana Class of 2026: Lana
11 Glazer, Eshaal Ali, Madelyn Ryan, and Mia Tsugawa of
12 Chesterton High School; Samor Dumas, Oliver Dunn, Julianna
13 Kralj and A'liegha Harper of Portage High School; and
14 Katelyn O'Neal, Grace Cornett, Natalie Dobos, and Alyssa
15 Bechinske of Westville Middle/High School;
2026 DR 3841/DI ol

2
1 Whereas, By allowing high schools to identify up to four
2 outstanding scholars during their junior year, the program
3 aims to increase their visibility and scholarship opportunities;
4 Whereas, The Rising Stars of Indiana program recognizes
5 students who demonstrate exceptional academic achievement,
6 leadership, and community service, and the selection criteria
7 includes enrollment in advanced classes, achievements in
8 standardized tests, and participation in extracurricular
9 activities; and
10 Whereas, These qualities are essential for students to be
11 chosen as Rising Stars of Indiana, highlighting their potential
12 for future success and leadership roles while demonstrating
13 exceptional qualities and involvement in community service:
14 Therefore,
15 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
16 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
17 SECTION 1. That the Indiana State Senate recognizes
18 the four individual students from Chesterton High School,
19 Portage High School, Westville Middle/High School.
20 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby
21 directed to transmit copies of this Resolution to Lana Glazer,
22 Eshaal Ali, Madelyn Ryan, and Mia Tsugawa of Chesterton
23 High School; Samor Dumas, Oliver Dunn, Julianna Kralj,
24 and A'liegha Harper of Portage High School; and Katelyn
25 O'Neal, Grace Cornett, Natalie Dobos, and Alyssa Bechinske
26 of Westville Middle/High School.
